Message-ID: <f9999aeddb15463cb59452d0f5b6088b@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>

Dear Divya,

If y_i ~ N(theta_i, v_i), then for any constant c, c*y_i ~ N(c*theta_i, c^2 * v_i).

So, it would be yi_new = yi/log(2) and vi_new = vi/log(2)^2.

Best,
Wolfgang

